It's time to give the bedroom a complete makeover. This is the last room in the house that only did a simple decoration.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and hearth. Close up the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customise an wardrobe.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch first...
The messy stage has passed.
Found a few dead birds behind the chimney, their bodies have dried up :(
Preparing to welcome the grey-washing work next week
Satisfied with the small alcove next to it
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing yet 🙈)
Ha ha, let's see what we found behind the radiator!
Still remember we added the cute ventilation holes to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep 把烟囱盖和烟囱帽都装好了。那些喜欢在烟囱里筑巢的白嘴鸦以后应该会更安全了
The chimney sweep has finished the job. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The softwood underlayment is already laid, and I've made a attachment for the vacuum cleaner using a toilet paper roll to suck up sawdust.  😂
Part of the floor is organized, and we can start laying it. Let's take a break and have a cup of tea first.
Uh, today's progress is a bit slow because I have to cut around the door frames for seamless integration with the hallway (which is also being floored), and it's quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me
We finally finished, but the assembly is a mess! What's more, the instructions for assembling the new bed are also terrible. Tonight, I'll be able to sleep well at last!
We still have to deal with the hallway floor and the baseboards. The renovation workers only came a month after we finished, so we have to make do with what we have now. The room is just bare plasterboard.
Yesterday, we did a simple DIY job in the evening, using a saw and a chisel to cut away a part of the door frame. This way, the flooring can be perfectly laid down below it.
The softwood underlay for the hallway has also been laid.
We laid the hallway floor yesterday, and took off at 5 am this morning to pick up the package at Heathrow Airport. I slept an afternoon nap and now I can finally start laying the baseboards for the hallway. I'll fill in the gaps later when the adhesive has dried.
